      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my 2018 toyota camry is making this really high pitched squealing sound when i hit the brakes, mostly when i'm slowing down for stop signs or going slow in parking lots. it's coming from the front passenger side. any idea what it could be?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The high-pitched squealing sound, often referred to as a \"squeal\" or \"screech,\" is a common symptom that can be caused by a few different issues. It's possible that the brake pads on the front passenger side are worn down, causing the brake caliper to rub against the rotor, resulting in the squeal. You might also want to check the brake fluid level, as low levels can cause the brake pads to vibrate and produce a high-pitched noise. It's a good idea to have a mechanic inspect the brake system to determine the root cause of the issue.",
